/span><hr size=1> is there any way whatsoever to raise thurgadin faction without hurting kael faction? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/01 10:24:44 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thurgadin faction question</span><hr size=1> don't think so....but you can kill giants/wolves outside Kael until you got enough Coldain faction, then go kill Dragons to get the Kromzek/Rif back up again.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utannblackpoint.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tann Blackpoint</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/01 1:08:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thurgadin faction question</span><hr size=1> dragons won't raise rif faction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrazaak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazaak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/01 1:24:25 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thurgadin faction question</span><hr size=1> I think your only hope would be to buy Coldain heads to keep giant faction up while killing Kromrif to keep Coldain faction up.<br>
<br>
That assumes that the positive Kromzek/Kromrif hits from Coldain heads are higher than the negative Coldain hit it gives, which is probably the case, since secondary hits are almost always smaller than primary hits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fortis>Fortis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/01 11:41:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thurgadin faction question</span><hr size=1> Turning in coldain heads to Captain Bvellos does not give negative coldain faction.  However the gain in 'rif faction is very very small (30 heads moved me from max scowling with Zek to ~Warmly, all the while never breaking me out of scowling with 'rif).<br>
<br>
Captain Bvellos gives:<br>
+Kromzek<br>
+Kromrif<br>
+KingTormax<br>
-Claws of Veeshan<br>
<br>
Kromrif Recruiter gives a much larger +Kromrif, but it also gives a -Coldain (significant).<br>
<br>
It would be quite a juggling act to try to balance your Coldain, Kromzek, and Kromrif factions, and most likely not worth your (or anyone's) time.  If you're worried about keeping giant faction for future quests, I would strongly suggest just blowing it away now for your needs atm, and worry about giant faction later after you get some quest armor pieces from ToV <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Fortis &lt;Harmonium&gt;<br>
* Grandmaster of the Ashen Order<br>
* Xev server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utannblackpoint.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tann Blackpoint</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/01 11:59:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thurgadin faction question</span><hr size=1> All you need really is zek and tormax faction  screw the frosties. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaegulmistweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daegul Mistweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/12/01 2:27:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thurgadin faction question</span><hr size=1> What about the icepaw kobald quests?  Faction hits for those? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unruter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nruter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/12/01 3:00:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thurgadin faction question</span><hr size=1> I dont think 30 heads will do it anymore.  I was max Scowl and turned in 66 heads so far as well as close to 60 kobold paws and I am still warmly with Zek and KOS to other two factions.  I also did some WW and TOV hunting during this time to help the faction along.<br>
<br>
I am still trying to maintain ally with Coldains but may give up very shortly, much too much time spent gathering these heads for such a little gain.<br>
